21/04/2003
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The prime ministers of the two BiH entities -- Republika Srpska's Dragan Mikerevic and the Federation of BiH's Ahmet Hadzipasic -- met in Banja Luka on Friday (18 April) to discuss issues related to the reform process. They agreed that representatives of the entity governments would meet within 15 days to settle the remaining draft amendments recommended by the Office of the High Representative's Bulldozer Committee. Mikerevic and Hadzipasic agreed that stimulating domestic production and creating a single economic space in BiH should be the main priorities of their governments. (RTRS - 18/04/03)
